        <!-- Q4 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>f(x)</m> 是可导函数, 且 <m>f(0)=f^{\prime}(0)=1</m>, 求 <m>\lim _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(\sin x)-1}{\ln f(x)}</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    【分析】这是 “<m>\frac{0}{0}</m>” 型的极限, 注意到 <m>f^{\prime}(0)=1</m>, 且 <m>x \rightarrow 0</m> 时, <m>\ln f(x)=\ln [1+f(x)-1] \sim f(x)-1</m>, 利用导数定义与等价无穷小代换求解.</p>

                <p>解: <me>\begin{aligned}
                    \lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(\sin x)-1}{\ln f(x)}&amp;=\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(\sin x)-f(0)}{\sin x} \cdot \frac{\sin x}{\ln [1+f(x)-1]}\\&amp;=f^{\prime}(0) \lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{x}{f(x)-1}\\&amp;=\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{1}{\frac{f(x)-f(0)}{x}}=1 .
                \end{aligned}
                </me>
                <p>【评注】本题主要考察函数在某一点的导数定义以及等价无穷小的代换.</p>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q5 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>f(x)</m> 在 <m>x=0</m> 处可导, 且 <m>f(0)=1, f^{\prime}(0)=2</m>, 求 <m>\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow \infty}\left(f\left(\frac{1}{x}\right)\right)^{\frac{\frac{1}{x}}{2-\cos {\frac{1}{x}}}}</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解: 令 <m>t=\frac{1}{x}</m>, 原式 <m>=\lim\limits _{t \rightarrow 0}[1+(f(t)-1)] \frac{t}{1-\cos t}</m>, 考虑到等价无穷小替换</p>

                    <p><m>\lim\limits _{t \rightarrow 0} \frac{(f(t)-1) t}{1-\cos t}=2 \lim _{t \rightarrow 0} \frac{(f(t)-f(0))}{t-0}=2 f^{\prime}(0)</m>, 由重要极限得, 原式 <m>=\mathrm{e}^{2 f^{\prime}(0)}=\mathrm{e}^{4}</m>.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q6 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    讨论函数<m>f(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{ll}
                    x \sin \frac{1}{x}, &amp; x \neq 0, \\
                    0, &amp; x=0
                    \end{array}\right.</m> 在 <m>x=0</m>> 处的连续性与可导性.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解:
                    <me>
                    \lim _{x \rightarrow 0} f(x)=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0} x \sin \frac{1}{x}=0=f(0) 
                    </me></p>

                    <p>故 <m>f(x)</m> 在 <m>x=0</m> 处连续.</p>

                    <p><me>
                    f^{\prime}(0)=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x)-f(0)}{x-0}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{x \sin \frac{1}{x}}{x}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0} \sin \frac{1}{x}
                    </me></p>

                    <p>不存在, 故 <m> f(x) </m> 在 <m> x=0 </m> 处不可导.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q7 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    当 <m>a, b</m> 为何值时, 函数<m>f(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{ll}
                    x^{2}, &amp; x \leq 1, \\
                    a x+b, &amp; x \gt 1
                    \end{array}\right.</m>在 <m> x=1 </m> 处可导?
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解: 要使 <m>f(x)</m> 在 <m>x=1</m> 处可导, 必须使 <m>f(x)</m> 在 <m>x=1</m> 处连续, 于是有
                    <me>
                    \lim _{x \rightarrow 1^{+}} f(x)=f(1)=1, 
                    a+b=1, \Rightarrow b=1-a .
                    </me></p>

                    <p>要使 <m>f(x)</m> 在 <m>x=1</m> 可导, 必须使 <m>f_{-}^{\prime}(1)=f_{+}^{\prime}(1)</m>,
                    而 <m>f_{-}^{\prime}(1)=\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 1^{-}} \frac{f(x)-f(1)}{x-1}=\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 1^{-}} \frac{x^{2}-1}{x-1}=2</m>,
                    <me>
                    f_{+}^{\prime}(1)=\lim _{x \rightarrow 1^{+}} \frac{f(x)-f(1)}{x-1}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 1^{+}} \frac{(a x+b)-1}{x-1}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 1^{+}} \frac{a(x-1)}{x-1}=a 
                    </me></p>

                    <p>于是 <m>a=2, b=1-a=-1</m>.
                    因此, 当 <m>a=2, b=-1</m> 时, <m>f(x)</m> 在 <m>x=1</m> 处可导.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q8 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设函数 <m>f(x)</m> 有连续的导函数, <m>f(0)=0, f^{\prime}(0)=b</m>, 若: <m>F(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{ll}\frac{f(x)+a \tan x}{x}, &amp; x \neq 0, \\ A, &amp; x=0\end{array}\right.</m>在 <m>x=0</m> 处连续, 求 <m>A</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解 :
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    &amp; \lim _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x)+a \tan x}{x} \\
                    = &amp; \lim _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x)}{x}+\lim _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{a \tan x}{x} \\
                    = &amp; \lim _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x)-f(0)}{x-0}+a \\
                    = &amp; f^{\prime}(0)+a \\
                    = &amp; a+b .
                    \end{aligned}
                    </me></p>

                    <p>又因为 <m>\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 0} F(x)=A</m>, 所以 <m>A=a+b</m>.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q9 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>f(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{ll}\frac{2}{a} a^{x}+1-\frac{2}{a}, &amp; x \leqslant 0, \\ \frac{\sin x}{x}, &amp; x \gt 0\end{array}(a \gt 0, a \neq 1)\right.</m>, 求 <m>f^{\prime}(x)</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解: 当 <m>x \lt 0</m> 时, <m>f^{\prime}(x)=\frac{2}{a} \ln a \cdot a^{x} ; x \gt 0 </m> 时, <m> f^{\prime}(x)=\frac{x \cos x-\sin x}{x^{2}}</m>.</p>

                    <p><me> f^{\prime}(0)=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0^{-}} \frac{f(x)-f(0)}{x-0}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0^{-}} \frac{\frac{2}{a} a^{x}+1-\frac{2}{a}-1}{x}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0^{-}} \frac{\frac{2}{a}\left(a^{x}-1\right)}{x}=\frac{2}{a} \ln a ; </me></p>

                    <p><me> f^{\prime}(0)=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0^{+}} \frac{f(x)-f(0)}{x}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0^{+}} \frac{\frac{\sin x}{x}-1}{x}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0^{+}} \frac{\sin x-x}{x^{2}}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0^{+}} \frac{\cos x-1}{2 x}=0 </me></p>

                    <p>因为 <m>f_{-}^{\prime}(0) \neq f_{+}^{\prime}(0)</m>, 所以 <m>f^{\prime}(0)</m> 不存在, 故 <m>f^{\prime}(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{ll}\frac{2}{a} \ln a \cdot a^{x}, &amp; x \lt 0, \\ \frac{x \cos x-\sin x}{x^{2}}, &amp; x \gt 0 .\end{array}\right.</m>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q10 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>y=\ln \cos x^{2}</m>, 求 <m>\frac{\mathrm{d} y}{\mathrm{~d} x}</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解: 设 <m> y=\ln u, u=\cos v, v=x^{2} </m>, 则
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    \frac{\mathrm{d} y}{\mathrm{~d} x} &amp; =\frac{\mathrm{d} y}{\mathrm{~d} u} \frac{\mathrm{d} u}{\mathrm{~d} v} \frac{\mathrm{d} v}{\mathrm{~d} x}=\frac{1}{u} \cdot(-\sin v) \cdot 2 x \\
                    &amp; =-\frac{2 x \sin x^{2}}{\cos x^{2}}=-2 x \tan x^{2} .
                    \end{aligned}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q11 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    证明 <m>\left(x^{\alpha}\right)^{\prime}=\alpha x^{\alpha-1},(x \gt 0, \alpha \in \mathbf{R})</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    证 
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    \left(x^{\alpha}\right)^{\prime} &amp; =\left(\mathrm{e}^{\ln x^{\alpha}}\right)^{\prime}=\left(\mathrm{e}^{\alpha \ln x}\right)^{\prime}=\mathrm{e}^{\alpha \ln x}(\alpha \ln x)^{\prime} \\
                    &amp; =x^{\alpha} \cdot \alpha \frac{1}{x}=\alpha x^{\alpha-1} .
                    \end{aligned}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q12 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    求 <m>y=\mathrm{e}^{(1-\sin x)^{\frac{1}{2}}}</m> 的导数.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解:
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    y^{\prime} &amp; =\left(\mathrm{e}^{(1-\sin x)^{\frac{1}{2}}}\right)^{\prime}=\mathrm{e}^{(1-\sin x)^{\frac{1}{2}}} \cdot(\sqrt{1-\sin x})^{\prime} \\
                    &amp; =\mathrm{e}^{(1-\sin x)^{\frac{1}{2}}} \cdot \frac{(1-\sin x)^{\prime}}{2 \sqrt{1-\sin x}} \\
                    &amp; =\mathrm{e}^{(1-\sin x)^{\frac{1}{2}}} \cdot \frac{-\cos x}{2 \sqrt{1-\sin x}} \\
                    &amp; =\frac{-\cos x}{2 \sqrt{1-\sin x}} \mathrm{e}^{(1-\sin x)^{\frac{1}{2}}} .
                    \end{aligned}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q13 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>y=\ln \frac{(x-1)^{3} \sqrt{1+x^{2}}}{x-3}</m>, 求 <m>y^{\prime}</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解: (先化简, 后求导!)
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    \because y &amp; =\ln \frac{(x-1)^{3} \sqrt{1+x^{2}}}{x-3} \\
                    &amp; =3 \ln (x-1)+\frac{1}{2} \ln \left(1+x^{2}\right)-\ln (x-3), \\
                    \therefore y^{\prime} &amp; =\frac{3}{x-1}+\frac{1}{2} \frac{2 x}{1+x^{2}}-\frac{1}{x-3} \\
                    &amp; =\frac{3}{x-1}+\frac{x}{1+x^{2}}-\frac{1}{x-3} .
                    \end{aligned}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q14 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>y=x \sqrt{\frac{1-x}{1+x}}</m>, 求 <m>y^{\prime}</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解: 两边取对数, 得
                    <me>
                    \ln y=\ln x+\frac{1}{2} \ln (1-x)-\frac{1}{2} \ln (1+x) .
                    </me></p>

                    <p>两边取对 <m>x</m> 求导, 得
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    &amp; \frac{y^{\prime}}{y}=\frac{1}{x}+\frac{1}{2} \frac{-1}{1-x}-\frac{1}{2} \frac{1}{1+x}=\frac{1}{x}-\frac{1}{1-x^{2}}, \\
                    \therefore &amp; y^{\prime}=y\left(\frac{1}{x}-\frac{1}{1-x^{2}}\right)=x \sqrt{\frac{1-x}{1+x}}\left(\frac{1}{x}-\frac{1}{1-x^{2}}\right) .
                    \end{aligned}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q15 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>y=\sqrt[x]{x}(x \gt 0)</m>, 求 <m>y^{\prime}</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解:法1 
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    y^{\prime} &amp; =(\sqrt[x]{x})^{\prime}=\left(x^{\frac{1}{x}}\right)^{\prime}=\left(\mathrm{e}^{\frac{1}{x} \ln x}\right)^{\prime} \\
                    &amp; =\mathrm{e}^{\frac{1}{x} \ln x}\left(\frac{\ln x}{x}\right)^{\prime}=\sqrt[x]{x}\left(\frac{1-\ln x}{x^{2}}\right) .
                    \end{aligned}
                    </me></p>

                    <p>法2
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    \ln y&amp;=\ln \sqrt[x]{x}=\frac{1}{x} \ln x \\
                    y^{\prime}&amp;=y\left(\frac{1}{x} \ln x\right)^{\prime}=\sqrt[x]{x}\left(\frac{1-\ln x}{x^{2}}\right)
                    \end{aligned}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q16 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>y=(1+\sin x)^{x}</m>, 则 <m>\left.\mathrm{d} y\right|_{x=\pi}=</m>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    【分析】本题为幂指函数求导, 幂指函数的求导 (或微分) 问题可化为指数函数求导或取对数后转化为隐函数求导.</p>

                    <p>解:法1 <m>y=(1+\sin x)^{x}=\mathrm{e}^{x \ln (1+\sin x)}</m>,于是
                    <me>
                    y^{\prime}=\mathrm{e}^{x \ln (1+\sin x)} \cdot\left[\ln (1+\sin x)+x \cdot \frac{\cos x}{1+\sin x}\right],
                    </me></p>

                    <p>从而 <m>\left.\mathrm{d} y\right|_{x=\pi}=y^{\prime}(\pi) \mathrm{d} x=-\pi \mathrm{d} x</m>.</p>

                    <p>法2 两边取对数得 <m>\ln y=x \ln (1+\sin x)</m>, 对 <m>x</m> 求导, 得 <m>\frac{1}{y} y^{\prime}=\ln (1+\sin x)+\frac{x \cos x}{1+\sin x}</m>,于是
                    <me>
                    y^{\prime}=(1+\sin x)^{x} \cdot\left[\ln (1+\sin x)+x \cdot \frac{\cos x}{1+\sin x}\right],
                    </me></p>

                    <p>故 <m>\left.\mathrm{d} y\right|_{x=\pi}=y^{\prime}(\pi) \mathrm{d} x=-\pi \mathrm{d} x</m>.</p>

                    <p>【评注】幂指函数的求导问题, 既不能单纯作为指数函数对待, 也不能单纯作为幂函数,而直接运用相应的求导公式.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q17 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    <m>y=f(x)</m> 有连续导数, 且 <m>f^{\prime}(x) \gt 0</m>. 已知 <m>f(1)=4, f^{\prime}(1)=3</m>, 则 <m>y=f\left(2 e^{x}-1\right)</m> 的反函数在 <m>y=4</m> 的导数 <m>\left.\frac{d x}{d y}\right|_{y=4}=</m>_____
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解: 
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    \left.\frac{d x}{d y}\right|_{y=4} &amp; =\frac{1}{\left.\left[f\left(2 e^{x}-1\right)\right]^{\prime}\right|_{x=0}} \quad \text { 由 } f(1)=4, \quad 2 e^{x}-1=1 \Rightarrow x=0 \\
                    &amp; =\frac{1}{\left.f^{\prime}\left(2 e^{x}-1\right) \cdot 2 e^{x}\right|_{x=0}}=\frac{1}{f^{\prime}(1) \cdot 2} \quad=\frac{1}{6} .
                    \end{aligned}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q18 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>f(x)</m> 在 <m>x=0</m> 处二阶可导, 且 <m>\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x)}{1-\cos x}=2</m>, 则  <m>f^{\prime}(0)= </m>_____
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解: 由 <m> 2=\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x)}{1-\cos x}=\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f^{\prime}(x)}{\sin x}=\lim\limits _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f^{\prime}(x)}{x} </m>,知 <m>f(0)  =0, f^{\prime}(0)=0 .</m></p>

                <p><me>
                \therefore f^{\prime \prime}(0)=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f^{\prime}(x)-f^{\prime}(0)}{x-0}=\lim\limits_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f^{\prime}(x)}{x}=2 .
                </me>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q19 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设 <m>y=x^{2} \mathrm{e}^{a x}</m> ( <m>a</m> 为常数), 求 <m>y^{(10)}</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解:
                    <me>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    y^{(10)}&amp;=\left(\mathrm{e}^{a x} \cdot x^{2}\right)^{(10)} \\
                    &amp;=\left(\mathrm{e}^{a x}\right)^{(10)} x^{2}+10\left(\mathrm{e}^{a x}\right)^{(9)}\left(x^{2}\right)^{\prime}+\frac{10 \times 9}{2 !}\left(\mathrm{e}^{a x}\right)^{(8)}\left(x^{2}\right)^{\prime \prime} \\
                    &amp;=a^{10} x^{2} \mathrm{e}^{a x}+10 a^{9} \mathrm{e}^{a x} \cdot 2 x+45 a^{8} \mathrm{e}^{a x} \cdot 2 \\
                    &amp;=a^{10} x^{2} \mathrm{e}^{a x}+20 a^{9} \mathrm{e}^{a x} \cdot x+90 a^{8} \mathrm{e}^{a x} \\
                    &amp;=\left(a^{2} x^{2}+20 a x+90\right) a^{8} \mathrm{e}^{a x} .
